<TITLE> CA gets three special assistants </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 10 (bdnews24.com)Three people were appointed as special assistants to the chief adviser Thursday, one of them said. They are former Bangladesh Power Development Board chairman MA Malek Mollah, Chakma Raja Debashish Roy and energy expert M Tamim. Prof Tamim confirmed the news to bdnews24.com by phone. Up to seven people will be appointed to the post with the status of state minister, chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed's press secretary Syed Fahim Munaim had said earlier. bdnews24.c
